{{- define "worktree-rules" -}}

WORKTREE RULES:
First, run: test -d {{.Worktree}}
Then:
- ALL file operations use {{.Worktree}}/ prefix (Read, Edit, Glob, Grep tools)
- All git commands MUST use: git -C {{.Worktree}}
- NEVER use the project root path for file operations
- Do not rewrite paths from FIRST ACTIONS or BOOTSTRAP CONTEXT — they are already resolved to the correct location
- The worktree root already ends in the task id — never prepend it inside (.worktrees/<id>/<id>/ is always wrong)
{{- if eq .RoleType "doer"}}
- File Read/Edit paths must match exactly — the edit tool tracks reads by string, not inode.
  Never retype or reconstruct the path.
- To CREATE new files: use Write directly without Read. Do not attempt Read first (it will error).
{{- else if eq .RoleType "reviewer"}}
- Do NOT modify git state: no git stash, git reset, git checkout, git commit, git clean, or any command that changes tracked files.
- To inspect base version of any file: git -C {{.Worktree}} show {{.BaseCommit}}:<path>
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
